It's hard to watch.

As a person born and raised in the great state of Ohio, it's embarrassing to see Jim Jordan as the representative for Ohio during the impeachment proceedings. How did it come to this? How was he elected? How is he STILL in office?

Gerrymandering.

And it's why I'm taking my experience and my momentum from my 2018 congressional race to run for the Ohio State Senate.

Until we elect people to the state legislature who will re-draw the districts fairly, we will see people like Jim Jordan in Congress.

The 2020 election is critical for making Ohio a true swing state again. In 2021, after the census, new Ohio laws give the legislature the opportunity to re-draw our districts and get rid of gerrymandering. Every seat we can flip in the state legislature next year will give us more of a say in how our congressional and state districts are drawn for the next ten years.

We can create a fair district for Jim Jordan instead of his current crazy duck-shaped district that meanders the state.

But we can't fight fairly without grassroots support.

Fair elections in Ohio are important not just to the future of Ohio but to the future of our country. I hope you can chip in to get Ohio on the right track.

